    <section id="id1163963996999">
      <title>[LO 1.13]</title>
      <list id="id1519120" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Make a loop at the end of a 2 m piece of string.</item>
        <item>Tie the loop around your rocket at its centre of gravity. Affix the loop with adhesive tape if necessary.</item>
        <item>The rocket should hang parallel to the ground surface (Sketch 1). Swing it around with a circular movement (Sketch 2).</item>
        <item>Change the centre of gravity or the centre of pressure until your rocket swings forward in a straight line while hanging horizontally.</item>
      </list>
      <figure id="id7815236">
        <media id="id7815236_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/Picture 12-bc13.png" id="id7815236__onlineimage" height="492" width="615"/>
        </media>
      </figure>
      <para id="id1163970515381">If you want to make any changes to your rocket to make it more stable, you can do it now. Decorate the bottles and fins so that it looks more like a rocket, for instance by painting it with an oil-based paint.</para>
      <para id="id1643311">Now you are ready to launch your rocket.</para>
    </section>
